<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Aspidophorodon longicornutum Qiao &amp; Xu sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of head B antenna C marginal processes of thoracic nota and abdominal tergites I-IV D ultimate rostral segment E oval sculptures of abdominal tergites F marginal process of abdominal tergite IV G siphunculus H spinal seta of abdominal tergite VIII I cauda J anal plate K genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702341" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aspidophorodon longicornutum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of head C antenna D ultimate rostral segment E hind tibia and tarsi F marginal processes of thoracic nota and abdominal tergites I-IV G oval sculptures of abdominal tergites H siphunculus I irregular wavy sculptures of abdominal tergite VIII J cauda K anal plate L genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702342" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7J</figureCitation>
